Had a party there last night with a group of friends in the front bar. Really catered for brilliantly by lovely staff and the place just has a great atmosphere.
Great bar with an amazing atmosphere! Great service and staff.
The refurbishments are fab. Lovely atmosphere and a great variety of drinks including cocktails.

This place is a fun place to chill and relax. They have a wide selection of beer and whiskey.  The music and ambience are well suited for this place. The servers are easy to chat with. They do their best make you feel at home and welcomed. The layout is simple and easy to navigate. There are benches for groups or stools for small groups.
An authentic centuries old pub serving a great selection of beer on tap, traditional Irish music and a fantastic historical comedy dinner show upstairs a few nights a week. Love this place!

I loved the ambience here... Nice place to go with friends who loves Irish music... I just fell in love with the group of people who sang and played different instruments with harmony... â¤ï¸â¤ï¸ Very pleasant staff.. varieties of beer.. altogether had a great time in this pub...
Great spot, great trad music, service was very good too- the place has character

Wow what a place full to the celling with Character. Old style Irish traditional pub. Full selection of beers and guest ales and beers. Fabulous friendly staff go above and beyond there service. Brilliant place for live music. Snugs here for private drinking. My favourite bar.

Really wholesome pub food. Big portions and a great price. Staff are super nice and helpful. Lots of clean comfortable seating and good parking. Book your table at the weekend to avoid disappointment as it can be quite busy.
Love this place good food great pints nice and clean. Very spacious

The Arches is by far and away the most underrated bar in Mallow. If you were to take this bar and put it in Cork City, it would be packed constantly. Amazing food, reasonable prices, a smoking area that covered and heated, has a pool table and a free jukebox.
Burgers are great! plenty of parking and very friendly staff! keep it up!
Great food fabulous staf always a warm welcome

Absolutely enjoyed every moment. Arrived just prior to 9pm on a summer Tuesday. Still busy. Back at the Locke today and Sophie did an awesome job of taking care of our group. I told her I wanted one of the T-shirts and she went out of her way to find just the one I wanted.

Had a fantastic evening here for my sister's hen. The menu was perfect and we had a nice quiet area to ourselves. The staff was very accommodating and friendly. They catered for different dietary requirements and last minute requests with a smile! They made our job as organisers so much easier. Would highly recommend for a fun party night.

A great place to hang out. Friendly staff, good food, drinks, live music. You can choose to sit inside or outside (located along the city canal). I was lucky enough to visit this place when there were live music and Riverdance show. A very popular place in Limerick City.
Great place. Such a popular och welcoming place. Lot's of space, both indoor and outdoor. We got a proper Irish live band with a dancer performing in the middle of the pub

Great place to sit outside when the weather is nice. There are lots of tables outside and the inside is quite large. Last weekend, the weather was nice and there was rugby on so the place was hopping. It seems like a good spot for watching a match/meeting up with a group of friends.
Good food and service. I visited for lunch. One of the things I liked is their menu, which is affordable. They even have a trio option. The staff is friendly. And I enjoyed the cheeseburger. ðŸ˜Š
Nice place to meet your friends and go crazy.. I mean, not so crazy haha but you can enjoy the music, drinks, good drinks and a beautiful garden outside. I do recommend!
Love the Pucan! Great place to watch the game. Tasty food. Great atmosphere and with good live bands.
Good pub, good atmosphere. Good for a stag or a hen. Nothing too special except the outdoor area. Great for a game
Great local pub! The first one I've been to when I arrived to Galway and I sure love coming back.

Great bar/restaurant located in the centre of Kilkenny town. Returning customer due to a recommendation from a work colleague. Went here again today and the food was absolutely top notch. The customer service honestly couldn't have being bettered either as the waiters were extremely attentive and knowledgeable of the menu. Would highly recommended this to anyone looking for a nice classy pub/sports bar and possibly interested in some really tasty food. This bar looks great as a sports bar and shows regular popular sports.
I love this place. The food is excellent and the staff are always outstanding, pleasant and so efficient. I would highly recommend.

On a recent trip to visit Kilkenny I was pleasantly surprised that Paris Texas has undergone extensive renovations! It had been years since I lived there so my memories of this place revolves around live music and good friends. It still has a familiarness but the new stuff makes it so much better!

Absolutely AMAZING food. One of the best pulled pork sandwiches I've ever had as well as the Lamb Clank. The live music can be heard throughout the entire venue which is just fantastic. Once you finish with your meal I HIGHLY recommend stopping by the Whiskey Bar to enjoy the music and company. Highly entertaining and interactive!

Just got back from the bar, wonderful experience! The music was lovely tonight full of folk songs and humour. The people were all very nice and the food was wonderful. I had the regular size chips and salsa as well as the steak tip fajita and it was enough for 3 people. The food and drinks were result available in good timing and the bar was full until around 8:30. I couldn't have imagine a better place to go in Kilkenny on an early night such a great cultural experience.
Great pub for beer and atmosphere! Always a great buzz. Nice local pub with good selection of beer wine and cocktails. They also serve coffee and a small food menu.
A friendly efficient, good humoured staff..I really enjoy every visit!
Cool people, great range of drinks and...love their Spritz on sunny days
Great place great vib to relax Sunday morning for coffee watch the world go by
Nice place. Always busy at the centre of city. Nicely decorated to have small party arrangements

A great little pub that's in something of a time warp. Original decor, no TV and no loud music. There's a fridge behind the bar with a selection of craft beers. Lots of character and a great spot for a sociable pint. The toilets are also in a time warp tho!

For generations Callanan's has been a quality authentic bar hidden away in the heart of the city. It has something for everyone, somehow happily mixing older locals with a younger modern crowd. It's a decent bar for everyone. There's also a traditional Cork 'Rings' board, but it may but be available on weekends when it's busy.
Hard to give it 5 stars as there wont be room for me anymore. Cracking boozer though. Long live Callanans.
Great bar. Unassuming in looks from outside. A hidden gem
One of a frightening few quintessential irish pubs, love it
Absolutely Amazing place to visit. Every person who served us was exceptional. Highly recommend.
One of the most iconic pubs in Cork. Many a happy pint I've had there over the years. Awesome staff and wonderful atmosphere...

Centre of Cork city only bar on Patrick's Street cork. Nice place to come sit with friends or on your own. Tight fit but very manageable not great for push chairs or Maybe even Wheel chairs narrow but wheelchair access from the front door as ramp here. Toilets upstairs bit of a climb but fine bar could watch Sport here. Drinks a bit on the High side. Get spot to sit and just chill out.
Great outdoir seating and atmosphere.very attentive staff and owner.
First stop on walking tour, had the best Irish Coffee ever! The owner said the recipe was a secret
Food is grand and kids eat free. Very reasonable price and staff are friendly. Menu includes gluten free options
Nice atmosphere and high standard of interior. The best place to go with friend visiting Ireland for a few days.

Nice pub, cheap drinks and always has live sports
Excellent local pub to have a few pints and hav a craic
Nice pub....a long get together place with a relaxed atmosphere
Did not get to bar today. Went to the shop. Small and quaint. A proper country shop should be like this. Serves locals perfectly.
Very homely. Owner is very nice and helpful. Atmosphere is quaint. Like an old Irish shop/pub should be. Should try the scones as they are extremely exquisite.
Little gem of a bar. Stop and say hi
Local pub and shop. Good for a bit of crack and catch a match on TV. Bar food as well if you get the munchies.

Pa Johnson 's is a great place to chill and relax.  They have live music and a decent selection of drinks. It is wheelchair accessible. The bathroom is wheelchair accessible. Didn't see wheelchair accessible parking.  It is a semi cozy and relaxing place. It is on the main street.
Pa's is a great place to go for pint and there's some great music on a Monday night well worth a visit.
Really nice bar with the cleanest toilets ever. Very comfortable place to sit and sip and chat
Very friendly staff and locals good choice of beers
Great bar sports available and very welcome bar staff
Great pint. Fantastic music. Nowhere better to spend a Sunday evening..
Perfect for the local boyo looking for a pint and some good tunes. Tourists beware :D
Ceol agus craic...fab little gem in mallow town... the bar staff cant be faulted. Its on the list if ever in mallow

Great little bar nestled at the back of the Clock house in Mallow. Nice pint of Guinness here. Good friendly staff. Easy going atmosphere leave your problems at the door. Great place to watch Sport on Wide Tv screens reasonable prices too. Offers on special occasions like major sporting events. Cosy bar open fire. Can get busy quickly as small enough bar. Live Music here too. Seating outside and inside.
A lovely place with nice people :)

Best place in Cork! This was my first day in Ireland for my honeymoon. My flight was cancelled and I had been up for over 30 hours fighting to get to Ireland. I was looking for a fun place with a local crowd. I found what I was looking for here. I spent the entire evening talking to nice people and learning about the local alcohol from the owner. I could not have asked for a better introduction to Ireland than coming here. Great beer selection, awesome live music and good vibe here. Definitely recommend coming here if you are traveling through Cork.
Fantastic Irish pub. We went on a Friday Evening they had two band. A traditional Irish folk band followed by a blues band. The selection of drinks is really good. A must visit in cork .
Excellent pub! Very fun experience and friendly owners. The trad session was excellent and rewarding. Please go visit when you are in Cork.
Fantastic Pub in the center of Cork! My pal and me enjoyed some pale ales and Gint's with live traditional Irish music! One of the reasons to visit Ireland again!
Great spot for a pint and a bit of music, friendly bar staff, cosy atmosphere!
Really nice atmosphere, with an aesthetic theme well portrayed. Staff seemed little slower/few in numbers but this may bother others more then some. Good food and drink served.
Grate food nice staff from eugenes bar shandon street
Nice food and good place to watch almost any sporting event. Can be absolutely jammers at times though, so get in early if it's a big game day
Had fun at quiz night. They have a good selection of beer and cider and the food was nice.
Everything you want from a bar. It even has a bowling alley!
Nice small pub with very friendly and helpful staff. Also the location in the center right next to the gallery is very convenient.
Beautiful selection of books. Staff very friendly!
Very good food and staff are very helpfull and friendly.
Love having an afternoon pint on the terrace here
Great pint.. good pubs for TV sport

nice local pub. we stopped in while walking around the city. good selection of local beers. only problem with the back garden area is all the smokers - you have to not mind smoke. staff very nice. recommend it if you're in the area.
Lovely friendly place with fantastic staff. Great food an lovely outdoor heated area. Always great craic
A gem of a pub. Loads of character, great staff, nice customers and good pints. It also has a decent size outdoor area.
Chilled out bar. Excellent smoking area even if your not a smoker. Good pints and friendly staff. Probably my favorite bar in Cork
Amazing, simply amazing. What a fantastic beer garden. I know, I always say good things about most pubs, but this place really is special !
Great staff great service great pizza

Nice casual local bar, the staff are really friendly and there is always a good vibe in there. It can be busy at weekends but never jam packed. They have a good selection of drinks including nice gin and tonics and a really nice pizza menu.
Love this place - staff are super friendly and the atmosphere is great. My fave pub in Cork

The transformation of the leaping salmon in the last year has been incredible! It is now one of the best spots in Cork for friends or familes alike to grab a few drinks or a bite to eat! Loved the veggie options which we demolished! Very friendly Irish hospitality! Served very quickly as we went for DUNCH (between lunch and dinner on the way to the airport)!
Good music, nice layout, plenty of nooks and crannies, good mix of people, local and otherwise. Competent and efficient bartenders.
Great pizza, thin crust. We loved it. They had great, friendly customer service.
Great atmosphere, friendly people. entertainment was great! one of my favorite spots can Cork.

If you want a real feel of a local bar, this is the place. You can call in for a pint and you will be left alone if that is what you seek. Or join in on the topic of conversation in hand. Simply meet your friends for a pint and a match. Real woody, comfy, fireplace feel bar with fantastic Ray's of light hitting all areas of the bar.
Authentic Cork pub with great selection of beer and lovely staff.
Best local bar in cork city.the staff are fab.its always great craic with the locals.and match days are always fun too
Great local bar, always a BBQ on for a big match or a buster, they create at atmosphere like a country pub in the city
Great atmosphere. Young and older. Chatty welcoming staff. Chieftain slurp.
Great craic, great prices , great local, really friendly.
Good clean bar, friendly staff and great pint at a good price

Very busy when Cork City are playing at home. It's newly refurbished so better than it was before. It has opened and closed a number of times in the past few years, so it's still early days as to whether it will stay open. Looks good from the outside.

What a great place. Love the new look. Great family run pub. So welcoming. Ideal for the Cork City soccer matches as its right on the doorstep. Would definitely recommend it so check it out. Definitely the best pint around and don't forget the drinks deals on a Sunday....happy days!
Great pint bar staff sound out
Moderate price. Great fresh food. Great service. One of the best Japanese experiences I've had in Dublin.
Good food, really friendly staff and great karaoke.

Easily the best value lunch and dinner in town. Ukiyo is bright and airy upstairs. Downstairs is spacious and very well laid out. Perfect for cocktails, dinner and dancing 7 nights a week! What makes Ukiyo super special besides the delicious food and drinks is the exemplary service with individual attention to detail. Every single member of staff are professional, charming and friendly. They go out of their way to make you feel special. There is only one U in Ukiyo ðŸ’š It's truly a magic place.
Wonderful ambiance and even better food and cocktails all topped off with great DJ and dancing!

Popped in for a Bento box last Friday lunchtime; havn't been in Ukiyo for ages and had forgotten how tasty the food is and what good value for money the Bento box is. Place was busy but service still v good..my friend was very impressed too. Will definitely be back sooner this time, priority will be to sample the cocktails in the new lounge downstairs.

Although busy at time. its one of the best pubs in town. cosy inside and big beer garden outside. A pleasing amount drinks to choose from. Its on the higher pricing side, but for the atmosphere its worth it.

Great pub. Quiz on a Thursday is fantastic. The quiz master even has his own rendition of happy birthday and does a dance if you let him know in advance. We often go in for a casual sour beer and pot of loose leaf tea on a Monday afternoon to watch the world go by. Lovely attention to detail by staff and great service with a smile

Really interesting pub, beer selection is limited, but a better choice than in the other nearby bars at time of writing. The coach yard that acts as a beer garden is unique and should be visited early evening or lunchtime.
Nice bar. Great pint of Amstell.
Friendly staff and nice atmosphere
Nice atmosphere in here. Lovely coffee and nice staff. It was nice to be able to sit outside. But I would prefer a non-smoking area outside.

Pretty fast lunch service with a typical menu. Upstairs is more of a bar scene with live music every night (at least in the summer)! I thought it was a fun place to go! At least check out the upstairs at night for live music.
What a treat!! We got to enjoy excellent traditional Irish music and Irish dancing! The music and show were both incredible, and the staff was friendly and inviting. Excellent place!

The service was excellent! From the hostess to the server, everyone was flexible and attentive. We had a large party that came in at different times and it was a busy night, but they accommodated us gracefully. The restrooms were clean and well stocked.

Busy spot but worth a visit. Grab a drink and try the ribs at the downstairs level dining room. Or head upstairs for pints and some live music with large stage and seating area, great for people watching and singing along.
Great little coffee shop. Good pastries, good selection of drinks and a nice spot to sit and take it all in
This place was gorgeous. Service and food was fantastic. Will be back when passing through again.
Beautiful little cafÃ© with lots of tasty treats. Always made feel welcome.
Lovely food and fast service with friendly staff even when they're busy. Recommended.
Great place to chill out and watch the world go by in clonakilty
Staff, menu, ambience all fantastic! Highly recommended for Brunch too..

Fantastic food , large portions . Eggs were cooked to perfection and full of flavor also great taste from the bacon and the avocado was perfectly ripe. Good value for money . My friends had the full Irish and couldn't praise the quality and taste enough . Staff were friendly.
Nice breakfast and seating area outside with quick enough service too.
First time in here, staff are excellent, professional & fun. Lively bar, definitely go back
Absolutely lovely food and friendly service. The portion sizes are on the big side so make sure you're hungry! Great value for money
Great pub, great pint and great atmosphere. One of my favorite pubs in Limerick.
Lovely place worth a visit for anyone wanting to find a nice pub with a good Pint
Great service by Natalie, we said group of six and it ended up being 10 of us, looked after us even though we'd lots of different orders and had questions about nearly everything on the menu.
Simply put a wonderful pub and great enviornment and staff.

This pub is a gem staff are all lovely customers likewise have to mention Andrew bar person handles customers with ease makes you very welcome all smiles but honestly all the guys and girls that work here are great keep up the good work.

Really enjoyed this pub. The atmosphere is really friendly and cozy. The beer selection is amazing and also the craft beers! We tried some and were really happy with our choices. The staff was helpful and nice.
Lovely old traditional Limerick pub, classic decor with lovely curved architecture. Great place for good craft beers. Not just your average bog standard drinks options
Great pub, fantastic range of drinks. Excellent staff. A great place to visit in Limerick.
Fab place cool vibe great craft bear and good gin and whisky list
Cool little neighborhood pub with friendly service and good prices.
A great pint without the modern distractions (loud music, TV's) found in most other pubs
Incredibly historic and beautifully kept. Nice beer and great staff
This place is great for a quiet pint. The atmosphere is very relaxed, the staff are very nice and the Guinness is great. Highly recommend a visit to experience it for yourself.

Superb little hideout in Cork. Cash only and in this case I like it. It brings you back a couple of years and a small price to pay for a great service. Very friendly place, feels comfy and relaxed. If you wanted a pint with a friend or a quiet drink its my number one spot. No pictures need - old irish pub is the only description you'll need!
Lovely little spot for a quiet Beamish and a catchup with friends.
A local pub for locals, full of village atmosphere. Old Ireland still lives on in here, which is great to see & hear in modern times... Highly recommended.
Great spot for a friendly Pint..
Excellent Guinness & hospitality
Great Irish pub great music
Best pint ever !

A great place for an authentic Irish experience minus all the tourist traffic. I'll never forget this night and the kind hospitality that waff shown to me by the locals. What av wonderful way to spend an evening in Dublin.

Grogan's has been popular for many many years and continues to be. The atmosphere is always lively especially outside as the crowds pass by. This is especially so at the weekends. The beer is good and it is not quite as crowded as some of the other pubs in the area. The location is great, right in the middle of the Dublin night life scene.

Cosy even when it's crowded. Lots of comings and goings, so if you scout things out you'll get a seat before too long. Interesting clientÃ¨le, a unique ambience, great Guinness, homemade toasted ham and cheese sandwiches, no music just chatter, decent bar staff, all make this an unmissable experience.
Have loved the cosy, friendly, eclectic feel of this place for many years. Excellent Guinness. Toasted sandwiches a throwback to the 70's in the best possible way

A classic stop while in Dublin. Be prepared for it to be busy. But it is worth it. Heaters outside make the cold days bearable and the patio is packed full on the sunny days. Inside is full of local artists work and cozy little seating areas. Don't forget a toasty cheese sandwich for the late night to keep you going! A must stop in Dublin!!

Really good bar food, tried few things and burger was huge and ok, cod was just lovely, yum chicken wings and delicious Cesar salad with fab garlic bread. The deserts were absolutely stunning and also must say that portions were just enormous!
Carvery was Fab. Great deal on a Sunday â‚¬35 for family 2 adults/2 children with icecream for the kids. Great value highly recommend.
Had my engagement party there. Great spot staff are great and the food was great too.

We had a leaving do for a couple of our staff. Bishoptowns Bar is a great place to have a do. They were very accommodating, reserving an area for us. Complimentary finger foods were served, also including a vegan plate, which was very much appreciated. Thank you. Staff were friendly and courteous. DJ was excellent. Great night was had by all. Would definately recommend this place for a night out.
Nice beer and food. Bingo is enjoyable on the Tuesday night although it's hard to navigate the number of stairs after afew beers!
Just went in for a drink and I really enjoyed it. The pint of Murphy's was lovely, service was good and the atmosphere was just like a traditional Irish pub.
Great place to drink the staff are top class and plenty of sport to watch on the various screens , I would recommend it lively pub at week ends.
Staff friendly, nice place for a drink. Open fire and outdoor area
Very good sport's bar 4 screens. Good sporting atmosphere.
Cool pub to watch the match. Only place I found in Kinsale that we could watch rugby.
Beautiful place. Excellent and friendly service. If 8 ever come back to Cork, this will be the first place to go. Thanks for everything
Great pint just like it was during the sixties

Wonderful experience with friendly staff and Jer the proprietor. I' ll be back.

Good place, lovely waiters, it's a amazing place to have a drink and maybe eat something, every now and then there is traditional live irish music, so for those who enjoy a bit of culture, it's worth a look.
Buy a drink, roll the dice, guess odd or even, win another drink or drinks to the same value... Only on Wednesday nights but we'll worth trying.. Nice smoking area, heated. Nice relaxed atmosphere
This is somewhere you end up after a big night out and just let lose and go for a dance. It's a little bit busy but the atmosphere was great

Great place to meet friends or colleagues for a nite out. They have a wide selection of beer and cocktails to choose from at the bar. It is wheelchair accessible and friendly. There are wheelchair accessible restrooms.
what a great place to relax #cocktails were of right mixture and staff friendly
One of the best spots in cork. Everyone should go at least once
Great bar. Seems quite popular. Fabulous outside area. Finger food is great and easy to set up tabs for multiple parties.
The company and the weather made it a fantastic place to be.
Love this pub. Lovely beer garden. Relatively fast service, even at the height of st patricks day. Would highly recommend
It is the place to be when there is a match. And if you like crowds. Huge garden, lots of space inside.
By far the best beer garden in Cork. Had the best day soaking up a bit of Ireland Summer Sun!
Fantastic bar friendliest staff you could meet great atmosphere

This a great place, great staff and maybe the best place for quite atmosphere or to watch a match. Grand place to have drink and here you will have wide choice of branded liquid, gin or pint. I will come back.
One of very few bars close to the city with real public house service. I highly recommend a visit.
Good service, friendly people, nice atmosphere, clean restrooms, ordered pizza from a nearby restaurant and enjoyed a good night with friends.
Great place anytime of the year. The staff are kind curious and most accommodating. The crossword is a lovely touch.
Fantastic food and service for a reasonble price. Steaks are particularly good!
Love Soos. Great selection of authentic street food dishes. Always delicious.
Nice place to drink. Great place to have a dance,  security are grand at the door,  clean place.
Always a great night here, good cocktails.
Very good food and friendly staff. Can't find words for the sundaes.

Nice pub. Looks small but stretches far back. Nice pint of Guinness. Good range of drinks on offer. Great atmosphere. Serves cocktail sausages and Black pudding after matches. Good place for groups. Large beer garden overlooking the River Shannon.
Nice pub to chill out. And they have the best guinness in town.
Love this pub! One of the best spots in Limerick for a post rugby match pint!
If you didn't know, this is the oldest pub in Limerick! Quaint little place that pours one of the best pints of Guinness in town.
Great pub for great company and best pint in limerick. Also the owners are lovely people.
Very interesting layout, with comfortable booths. love the set up for bands. Saw Woody and friends perform, such fun! Good beer selection and multiple bars so minimal queuing required.
Could spend the whole day just looking at all the different bottles of beers ales etc etc on the walls. Lovely food and even better atmosphere. Definitely next time will be going back there again.

A few friends and I went to Porterhouse for drinks like every other tourist in Dublin, and overall, despite everyone here basically being a tourist, it was enjoyable and the bar is huge. This is basically a four level bar, so even when the bar is packed with people, there is a lot of space.

Loved it. Enjoying a good meal while listening to great live Irish music. Friendly, good and fast service, as well, what more could you ask for. As we enjoyed it so much, we went there 2 days in a row.

Delicious food and a fun atmosphere can be had at Porterhouse Temple Bar. We ate her on our first night in Ireland, and again on our last night two weeks later. Weave your way through all the floors of the bar and head all the way up to the top floor for the restaurant. The food here is tasty and delicious, and they have the most amazing beer battered onion rings ever! Eat here... it's wonderful!
What a brilliant place. ALL about the music and atmosphere!

One of the best kept secrets in town. Tiny little cozy pub with amazing local musicians. If youâ€™re looking for a friendly, quaint and rustic little pub this is the place. Youâ€™ll remember your visit forever.
Best little pub in Ireland as in clonakilty west cork
Takes you back in time
A magical night, you can't describe. The Guinness tastes better with your music.

I've been to a few gay bars in Ireland, and I was expecting a dingy pub-like bar. Chambers is a nice bar with modern decor. My colleague and I met several people throughout the night; everyone was very friendly. I look forward to coming back!
Popped in during Corkfest for a minute as "Cassette" was playing. We loved the band and the bar was filled with people having fun. Wish I'd stayed longer actually.

We came across this bar as it seemed to be the only place in close proximity that was open and hoppin at 2-2:30am. We went in for a few drinks and some dancing. Definitely a good place when you want to stay out and keep the party going.
I never go to Cork without going for a night out in Chambers! Great atmosphere, great music, great staff and never a dull moment. Looking for the Craic, you found it!
Always great music, staff and crowd.

Just stopped off for dinner on the way home back to County Down amazing bit of food steak is always outstanding and so was the fish Iâ€™ve had. Thanks for the great custom and great food and hospitality.
Brilliant food and service. Cosy atmosphere.
Great buzz, good coffee and food.
Foods amazing and staff really friendly. Definitely be back next time in Dundalk.

Great food, great service & a pleasure to be in, I went to McGeoughs this evening with family and was very impressed with the friendliness of all the staff members, the relaxed atmosphere and the tasty dishes. Definitely will be back again!
